Western Cape police have confirmed that a shooting occurred at the Cape Town International Airport Wednesday morning. Police spokesperson Vish Naidoo said that the incident took place around 5:15 am at the drop and go section which the public has access to that particular area. “A man believed to be in his 50’s was shot and wounded in the upper body by unknown suspects,” said Naidoo. Naidoo indicated that after the shooting the suspects fled the scene and the victim was treated on scene and later taken to the hospital.  More to follow…. -TNA Reporter 